result.name: Grand Avenue Thai Café

reviews.text:
Typical.

Not bad, not good, your usual MSG restaurant. It's a bit too salty, but that is by design to hide the fact that there's too much sugar in the Thai milk tea.

So definitely flavorful, if you're looking at giving your digestive system a workout.

This restaurant is fairly woeful, it's like it can really be bothered to serve any purpose. The food was bang average, the staff were miserable, the customers were miserable, the menu was bland, more or less everything associated with this meal was unimpressive. More than one star just because my pineapple fried rice was moderately tasty. Describing this restaurant as extra medium would be too kind.
Tea set is rather expensive and quality is so so
It's 8:15pm, and they are running out of roasted mullet and Hainan chicken. The waitress is rude too.

The food was good and they had nice lunch sets. They were able to accommodate and make one vegetarian for me. The Thai ice tea was surprisingly flavorful too. My friends enjoyed their green curry, though it was spicy they agreed.

result.formatted_address: 1 Tong Tak Street, Tseung Kwan O, Hong Kong
result.name: Tseung Kwan O Plaza

reviews.text: Has everything you need incl movie theatre & air con, which is good during summer!

Worth visiting the small wet market for fresh fish, fruit and veg, frozen food, small supermarket and various other little shops. 

Prices are a little cheaper than Saikung and Hang Hau wet markets and the food quality the same. 

Upstairs in the main shopping mall expect to find all the usual brands plus restaurants. TKO Plaza connects to Popcorn 1&2 malls. 

TKO Plaza has changed the free parking mechanism in that only receipts proving credit card payment will be accepted.
Quite nice, big and different shops. Recommended for tourists.
I love the parking place, with enough spaces to each car, and reasonable daily parking, just $75 for 12hours, good?

A big mall for shopping and dining with a cinema and many popular outlets and brand names. Lots of public areas and parks nearby and it shares other malls under one roof by joined walkways and bridges. Great for when it rains and plenty of choices to shop and eat.

Right on top of mtr so easy to get to and conveniently located from hustle and bustle of HK Island.

result.name: 泰巷

reviews.text:
停業裝修個多月之後已於復活節(2019)前重新開業。雖說是装修，但其實没有怎麼改動。菜式也停業前也一樣，以港式泰國菜為主。除午餐和晚餐外，還設有下午茶餐時段。星期六、日，公眾假期更有早餐供應。

午市和晚市的菜牌好像是同一樣，以小菜為主，也有泰式小食，湯粉，炒飯/粉和飯類。選擇雖不算少，但也不是太多。停業前晚市主打的套餐選項，重開後就不見了。早餐和下午茶餐都是以港式西餐(多士，煎蛋，火腿等)，加湯粉麵為主。味度方面，無論早午晚餐，各線水平也算在中上。偶爾某有些菜式，也會有驚喜之作。當天晚飯，點了泰式豬手，海鮮炒河粉，小食拼盤和芒果糯米飯。豬手和海鮮炒河均保持水準。驚喜的是小食拼盤，無論串燒，春卷或泰式香蘭雞都非常好食。價錢算是平實，和茶餐廳相差不大。務服則是一般，不過要比茶餐廳好得多。(4/2019)

晚飯套餐實惠，水準也不錯。星期六日有早餐，街坊多一個選擇。(2017)
午餐性價比高！味道很不錯！份量也很足夠👏🏼要一來再來！
猪扒即炸色香味脆，㗎哩好味Good
早餐選擇很多，容易找位，價錢合理，質素一般。
味道可以再好一點， 肉類比較鞋 太嚡了
